-- Mercator Poslovni Appoints Balazic New CEO, Finance Reports
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-05-18T11:28:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/mercator-poslovni-appoints-balazic-new-ceo-finance-reports.html
Mercator Poslovni Sistem (MELR)  d.d. named
Toni Balazic to be chief executive officer of the Slovenian
supermarket chain, Finance newspaper  reported , without saying
where it obtained the information.  Balazic, who’s been at the helm of food company Zito d.d.,
will take the position at the retailer beginning June 1. He will
replace Ziga Debeljak, who stepped down in March over the
disputed sale of Mercator to its Croatian rival Agrokor d.d.,
the Ljubljana-based newspaper said.  Agrokor plans to make another offer for Mercator, Zagreb-
based Poslovni Dnevnik newspaper said on May 14 after  Croatia ’s
largest private company abandoned its previous bid in February
due to a protracted process.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
